Wilmington.Downtown Wilmington Commercial Historic: Delaware Avenue Historic District is a national historic district located at Wilmington, New Castle County, Delaware. It encompasses 44 buildings in the city's downtown, most on North Market Street between 6th and 9th Avenues. The district was the commercial center of the city between roughly 1870 and 1968, and contains an architecturally distinguished collection of late 19th and early 20th-century architecture.
